The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 October is 89,835 (10,354 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 October, there were 4,546 new confirmed cases (524.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 October, there were 3,284 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 38% (1,262 extra cases).
